data.title: First pictures of Rafael Nadal and wife Maria Francisca Perello

data.text:
One day after marrying Maria Francisca Perello, having dated for 15, Rafael Nadal has provided two photos through the Foundation that bears his name.

Both the religious ceremony and the subsequent celebration took place in Sa Fortalesa, a castle dating from the 17th century in the Pollenca area, north of the island of Mallorca.

Rosa Clara was the designer of Perello's wedding dress, while Nadal chose the Italian Brunello Cucinelli for such an important day.

Tomeu Catala, a close friend of the family, was the priest in charge of officiating the ceremony.

Among the illustrious guests were the former king of Spain, Juan Carlos I, singer Julio Iglesias, as well as fellow tennis players Feliciano Lopez, David Ferrer and Marc Lopez.
